sentences: Nancy Ames (born Nancy Hamilton Alfaro on September 30, 1937) is an American folk singer and songwriter.
Ames is the founder and creative director of the Houston, Texas, based event and production company, Ward & Ames, which she founded in 1982.
Ames was born in Washington, D.C., the granddaughter of Ricardo Joaquín Alfaro (1882–1971), who served as President of Panama from 1931-32.
By 1964 she was married to Romanian hypnotist Triaian Boyer.
By 1968, they had divorced.
Ames has resided in Houston, Texas since 1972.
She broke the top 100 twice in 1966; "He Wore the Green Beret," her answer song to Staff Sgt.
She is listed as the co-writer of the theme song to The Smothers Brothers Comedy Hour with Mason Williams per Williams' own 1969 LP entitled Music by Mason Williams.
Ames and Williams also co-wrote "Cinderella Rockefella," an international pop hit in 1968.
In 1982, Nancy and her current husband, Danny Ward, founded Ward & Ames, a full-service special events and video production firm.
